wikipedia_page.main: Frederic William Madden (9 April 1839 – 21 June 1904), son of Frederic Madden, was an employee of the British Museum and an authority on Roman, Jewish and Christian numismatics.

response: Frederic and Emily had six known children, the eldest being Frederic William Madden (1839–1904), who in 1860 married Elizabeth Sarah Rannie (1839–1893) and had four children.Census Returns of England and Wales, 1881. The National Archives of the UK, Kew, Surrey, England: Class: RG11; Piece: 1077; Folio: 51; Page: 32; GSU roll: 1341254 Frederic, a numismatist of note, was Secretary and Bursar of Brighton College 1874–88 and then Chief Librarian of the Public Library in Brighton 1888–1902.
